member.name: T:NEA_ICS.UserInterface.clsSorter`1
member.summary:
This instance class is used to sort a generic collection of object instances. It automatically fetches the type and performs the necessary comparison(s) to sort.
To use, instantiate this class, set the sort string property, and pass this instance to the internal Sort() function of your generic collection.
SOURCE CODE from http://blog.josh420.com/archives/2009/02/sorting-generic-list-dynamically-in-vbnet.aspx Example: Dim MyList As List(Of MyClassType) = 'Populate the list somehow Dim Sorter As New Sorter(Of MyClassType) ''' Sorter.SortString = "Field1 DESC, Field2" MyList.Sort(Sorter) 'After this call, the list is sorted

member.name: M:NEA_ICS.UserInterface.clsSorter`1.#ctor(System.String)
member.summary:
Instantiate the class, setting the sort string.
Example: "LastName DESC, FirstName"

member.name: P:NEA_ICS.UserInterface.clsSorter`1.SortString
member.summary:
The sort string used to perform the sort. Can sort on multiple fields. Use the property names of the class and basic SQL Syntax.
Example: "LastName DESC, FirstName"
